00:35:36.510 --> 00:35:39.370
Tomorrow, the futures price
will be different.

00:35:39.370 --> 00:35:43.260
And so, what they have in the
futures markets is daily

00:35:43.260 --> 00:35:45.380
settlement.

00:35:45.380 --> 00:35:50.960
And that means that if
I sold futures --

00:35:50.960 --> 00:35:53.960
I'm storing rice and
selling futures --

00:35:53.960 --> 00:35:55.405
if the price goes down --

00:35:58.410 --> 00:36:01.470
I'm sorry, if the
price goes up --

00:36:01.470 --> 00:36:03.330
it works against me,
because I've locked

00:36:03.330 --> 00:36:04.910
in the lower price.

00:36:04.910 --> 00:36:09.270
So, the broker debits my margin
account by the daily --

00:36:09.270 --> 00:36:11.670
every day they change
my margin account.

00:36:11.670 --> 00:36:15.040
So, if I've sold futures and the
price goes up, they take

00:36:15.040 --> 00:36:16.600
it out of my margin account.

00:36:16.600 --> 00:36:20.850
If the price goes down, they put
it into my margin account.

00:36:20.850 --> 00:36:24.550
And I can quickly deplete
my $5,000.

00:36:24.550 --> 00:36:26.280
The post price keeps going up.

00:36:26.280 --> 00:36:29.670
Then I say, gee, I wish I hadn't
signed that contract,

00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:31.970
because I could have waited
a few days and

00:36:31.970 --> 00:36:33.310
gotten a better price.

00:36:33.310 --> 00:36:36.630
Meanwhile, the broker calls you
on the phone and says, I'm

00:36:36.630 --> 00:36:39.460
sorry, your margin account
is almost depleted.

00:36:39.460 --> 00:36:41.055
Do you want to put
up more margin?

00:36:41.055 --> 00:36:44.400
And this is where you get the
reality of futures trading.

00:36:44.400 --> 00:36:47.900
Because there's no counterparty
risk.

00:36:47.900 --> 00:36:51.600
That means, that if you don't
put up more margin, the broker

00:36:51.600 --> 00:36:53.960
closes you out and says,
here's your money.

00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:55.770
Do you understand how
this works now?

00:36:55.770 --> 00:36:58.510
So, there's no counterparty
risk, because it doesn't

00:36:58.510 --> 00:37:01.890
matter, whether you're a drunk
or a sociopath, the broker has

00:37:01.890 --> 00:37:02.930
you trading.

00:37:02.930 --> 00:37:05.600
And it doesn't matter
at all what you do.

00:37:05.600 --> 00:37:08.830
Once you put up the money, and
if you just don't answer the

00:37:08.830 --> 00:37:11.840
phone -- if you, say you don't
answer the phone, the broker

00:37:11.840 --> 00:37:14.970
will close you out, when
the margin is depleted.

00:37:14.970 --> 00:37:17.290
So, the broker takes no risk.

00:37:17.290 --> 00:37:21.010
The counterparty is not
even given to you.

00:37:21.010 --> 00:37:23.290
You don't even know, who's
on the other side of that

00:37:23.290 --> 00:37:26.190
contract, because the other
side is making --

00:37:26.190 --> 00:37:30.160
you're both making a contract
with the exchange.

00:37:30.160 --> 00:37:33.430
And so, you don't care about
counterparty risk, and there's

00:37:33.430 --> 00:37:35.520
no risk to this contract.

00:37:35.520 --> 00:37:40.180
That means, these prices are
pure prices, and they don't

00:37:40.180 --> 00:37:43.040
have any counterparty risk.

