Now, this is kind of
theoretical, because I just

00:41:39.240 --> 00:41:41.940
told you, nobody ever knows
what the price today is

00:41:41.940 --> 00:41:44.990
anyway, because the only way
you ever know prices is

00:41:44.990 --> 00:41:46.030
through futures markets.

00:41:46.030 --> 00:41:47.670
But let's just think a little
bit abstractly.

00:41:47.670 --> 00:41:51.570
Say, there's a cash market
for wheat, that it's

00:41:51.570 --> 00:41:52.410
