maturity right here at the

00:45:34.580 --> 00:45:39.110
peak, just before the harvest.
But if there were no

00:45:39.110 --> 00:45:43.030
uncertainty, the futures price
would just be constant

00:45:43.030 --> 00:45:46.190
throughout that whole time.

00:45:46.190 --> 00:45:49.490
It would always equal the
expected spot price on that

00:45:49.490 --> 00:45:50.740
future date.

00:45:53.480 --> 00:45:57.750
And again, it would repeat
the next year.

00:45:57.750 --> 00:46:00.520
Futures contracts have no
expected price change in this

00:46:00.520 --> 00:46:01.770
perfect world.

00:46:06.440 --> 00:46:07.560
Do you see what I'm saying?

00:46:07.560 --> 00:46:10.950
This equation always holds,
because, as this contract

00:46:10.950 --> 00:46:16.120
