00:51:24.910 --> 00:51:29.780
And this is what we call
the price of oil.

00:51:29.780 --> 00:51:33.920
When you hear oil prices quoted
on TV or on magazines,

00:51:33.920 --> 00:51:36.550
they're quoting the front
month futures.

00:51:36.550 --> 00:51:38.300
Let me be clear about that.

00:51:38.300 --> 00:51:43.210
Oil is mostly sold on
long-term contracts.

00:51:43.210 --> 00:51:46.410
So, just like our rice merchant,
